<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="604" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 868.001 G 29/3.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chargé d’Affaires of
                                    Greece</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Royal Greek Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I make it my painful duty to inform your excellency that my Sovereign,
                            George I, King of the Hellenes, died yesterday at Saloniki, in the
                            afternoon, from the effects of an attempt on His August Person.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">A. Vouros</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>